column4: Would one of you kind ladies and gentlemen help me out w/ something?  I'm trying to install a software modem. I did scanModem and it tells me I need a Lucent driver (I think), so I'm going by the DialupModemHow to on the wiki and on the step where you type in "sudo modprobe lt_serial" I get an eror saying "Module Lt_serial not found".  The previous steps went ok. I'm using Ubuntu version 5.10.
Does anybody know at the support IRC channel for Ubuntu linux is?
did you type that with the caps?
No I typed in all lower case
sorry no clue, i don't use a modem anymore
what-s the url for the guide
